Identicies in Intranet and Internet scenario:
----------------------------------------------
Client Identity => Is the caller to the WCF service. 
we are going to see 3 various Identities in both Intranet and Internt scenarios

3 Identities are 
-----------------
1. Token/Host Identity (Identity of a Host Process - Identity used to access resourses (filesystem ,registry, DbAccess) 
2. Principle Identity
3. Windows Identity 

For Browser based Intranet applications 
the Principle Identity/clinet Idetnity are IIS/ AppPool, you need to do soft Impersonation. 
Actullay user(MACHINENAME/RAJA) is calling from broser (Assuming it is hosted on IIS). 

